## Build

```bash
make build
```

Open a container shell:

```bash
make shell
```

`make build` and `make shell` use `tools/mmwave-run`. The runner starts a
disposable Docker container with a clean environment, `HOME=/tmp/mmwave-home`,
and `bash --noprofile --norc` for interactive shells. It does not source or
modify host `.bashrc`, `.zshrc`, profile files, or host TI installs.

Clean generated output:

```bash
make clean
```

Output binary:

```text
build/app/@OUTPUT_BIN@
```

## Source Layout

```text
app/
  makefile
  mss/      # present when the forked demo has MSS sources
  dss/      # present when the forked demo has DSS sources
tools/
  mmwave-run
```

The build uses the forked demo's original TI makefile. If a demo only has MSS,
only MSS is built; if it has MSS+DSS, the SDK makefile drives both cores and
metaimage generation.

